1
00:00:11,041 --> 00:00:12,875
[SENDA]
His whole team?

2
00:00:12,958 --> 00:00:14,166
Well, that's unfortunate,

3
00:00:14,250 --> 00:00:16,000
but I'm sure Kanoichi did
what he could.

4
00:00:16,083 --> 00:00:18,958
After all, his plan
was good enough for you, right?

5
00:00:20,708 --> 00:00:23,583
I'm sorry? No, I don't think
we can do that.

6
00:00:28,750 --> 00:00:32,000
We sent Miyako there,
but Kanoichi told him

7
00:00:32,083 --> 00:00:33,708
to stay out of it,
so that's that.

8
00:00:36,916 --> 00:00:39,666
With all due respect, we've got
our own work to complete.

9
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:41,583
I can't just lend
my subordinates

10
00:00:41,666 --> 00:00:43,583
to mop up your mess.

11
00:00:43,666 --> 00:00:45,416
I understand they're in danger,

12
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:47,166
but I'm afraid
there's nothing we can do.

13
00:00:47,250 --> 00:00:49,166
It's outside
of our jurisdiction.

14
00:00:49,250 --> 00:00:52,416
Of course, if that area ended up
being turned over to us,

15
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:54,500
we may be able to help you out.

16
00:00:54,583 --> 00:00:55,708
Best of luck.

17
00:00:59,125 --> 00:01:00,166
[sighs]

18
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:03,458
[cell phone buzzing]

19
00:02:37,208 --> 00:02:39,666
[THEO] The whole cocoon
operation was wiped out?

20
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:40,958
What happened?

21
00:02:41,041 --> 00:02:42,833
[FAIRIES]
She's mad, she's mad,

22
00:02:42,916 --> 00:02:44,291
she's really mad!

23
00:02:44,375 --> 00:02:46,291
-You stupid human jerks!
-Ow!

24
00:02:46,375 --> 00:02:47,833
Manari's angry!

25
00:02:48,958 --> 00:02:51,583
Our offerings!
They are gone!

26
00:02:51,666 --> 00:02:55,208
You people made the
Silkworm Princess super angry!

27
00:02:55,291 --> 00:02:57,375
Now we'll all have to leave
our home because of you!

28
00:02:57,458 --> 00:02:59,208
[FAIRIES]
You dummies!

29
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:02,791
What offerings
was she talking about?

30
00:03:02,875 --> 00:03:06,083
Uh! Did you say "offerings"?
Is that why they looked so mad?

31
00:03:06,166 --> 00:03:07,750
[ARATA]
Yeah, pretty sure.

32
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:10,041
Crap, this is serious!

33
00:03:10,125 --> 00:03:11,916
Those cocoons were going
to be turned

34
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:14,000
into offerings for a god!

35
00:03:14,083 --> 00:03:15,708
For a god?

36
00:03:15,791 --> 00:03:17,291
[cell phone buzzing]

37
00:03:20,791 --> 00:03:21,750
[SENDA]
I see.

38
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:24,000
Tell me, Arata,

39
00:03:24,083 --> 00:03:25,250
have you ever heard of deities

40
00:03:25,333 --> 00:03:27,041
known as Oshira-sama?

41
00:03:27,125 --> 00:03:29,708
-[ARATA] Huh?
-They're silkworm gods.

42
00:03:29,791 --> 00:03:31,666
I'd rather be stuck
dealing with demons.

43
00:03:31,750 --> 00:03:34,666
Right, demons are dangerous,
but they can be exorcised.

44
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:36,625
Gods, on the other hand though.

45
00:03:36,708 --> 00:03:38,208
They can be a real handful.

46
00:03:39,208 --> 00:03:41,791
And when they get mad, they
start throwing around curses.

47
00:03:41,875 --> 00:03:43,416
[ARATA]
Curses?

48
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:45,958
[THEO] I doubt we get off
with just a curse after this.

49
00:03:46,041 --> 00:03:49,000
Worst case scenario,
they become tatarigami,

50
00:03:49,083 --> 00:03:50,291
and then we're really screwed.

51
00:03:50,375 --> 00:03:52,458
Gods can be appeased
with rituals.

52
00:03:52,541 --> 00:03:55,875
We can usually pull one off
before things get too bad.

53
00:03:55,958 --> 00:03:58,875
But the rituals can be hard
to carry out correctly,

54
00:03:58,958 --> 00:04:00,750
and it's not like
we can just...

55
00:04:02,791 --> 00:04:05,041
-[THEO] Don't tell me!
-Yeah.

56
00:04:05,125 --> 00:04:07,083
Our friends from
City Hall need us.

57
00:04:07,166 --> 00:04:09,000
They foolishly made
a god angry.

58
00:04:09,083 --> 00:04:10,958
And only the Ears
of Sand can help.

59
00:04:11,041 --> 00:04:13,166
Why the hell would
you agree to that?

60
00:04:13,250 --> 00:04:16,083
It's on the verge
of becoming a tatarigami!

61
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:17,166
[SENDA sighs]

62
00:04:18,291 --> 00:04:19,750
-[ARATA] Okay. I'll do it.
-Huh?

63
00:04:20,750 --> 00:04:22,500
It'll be fine.

64
00:04:22,583 --> 00:04:24,750
-Seriously?
-Honestly, I'm terrified,

65
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:28,791
but things will only
get worse unless I go.

66
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:34,583
If there's anything I can do,
anything at all, I'm in.

67
00:04:34,666 --> 00:04:35,916
[THEO groans]

68
00:04:37,166 --> 00:04:40,458
♪

69
00:04:40,541 --> 00:04:43,416
Are you sure? No doubts?

70
00:04:44,541 --> 00:04:45,416
None.

71
00:04:48,083 --> 00:04:49,708
[SENDA] All right.
You pull this off,

72
00:04:49,791 --> 00:04:52,000
and City Hall
will owe us a solid.

73
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,416
[ARATA]
Right!

74
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,500
[SATORU] Of course
the brood mother was nearby.

75
00:05:03,583 --> 00:05:04,666
I got careless.

76
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,708
This Kekkaiseki

77
00:05:07,791 --> 00:05:10,083
lets me kill Anothers
with my own hands.

78
00:05:11,458 --> 00:05:13,875
You're no different
from any other bug,

79
00:05:13,958 --> 00:05:15,375
just vermin to be crushed.

80
00:05:15,458 --> 00:05:17,083
[chitters]

81
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:22,250
If you're actually trying
to talk to me, don't bother.

82
00:05:28,208 --> 00:05:29,500
You're staying right there.

83
00:05:30,541 --> 00:05:31,666
You've hurt people.

84
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:32,958
You've wrecked this place.

85
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:34,708
Now it will become your grave.

86
00:05:35,708 --> 00:05:38,208
When will you accept
that you can't win?

87
00:05:38,291 --> 00:05:41,458
This world belongs to us,
Another, not your kind!

88
00:05:41,541 --> 00:05:43,750
Your time ended long ago,
and our era...

89
00:05:44,791 --> 00:05:45,916
is now!

90
00:05:48,958 --> 00:05:51,000
[shrieks]

91
00:05:53,041 --> 00:05:55,500
Please don't!
You have to stop!

92
00:05:55,583 --> 00:05:59,208
Whatever you came here to do,
you're too late.

93
00:05:59,291 --> 00:06:01,208
[grunting]

94
00:06:04,041 --> 00:06:06,208
-I told you to back off!
-You fool!

95
00:06:06,291 --> 00:06:08,500
[ARATA]
Don't hurt her anymore!

96
00:06:08,583 --> 00:06:09,791
"Hurt her?"

97
00:06:09,875 --> 00:06:11,791
It's not a person. It's a thing.

98
00:06:11,875 --> 00:06:14,208
A dangerous Another
that needs to die.

99
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:15,625
Don't interfere!

100
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:18,083
You're just looking
for an excuse to kill her!

101
00:06:18,166 --> 00:06:21,375
Your hatred isn't helping here,
it's making things worse!

102
00:06:21,458 --> 00:06:22,583
[SATORU]
I'm sick of this.

103
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:26,291
Then why don't you sit back
and let me do my job?

104
00:06:26,375 --> 00:06:28,375
What. Your job?

105
00:06:28,458 --> 00:06:31,083
[cell phone buzzing]

106
00:06:31,166 --> 00:06:33,208
Who would be calling right now?

107
00:06:33,291 --> 00:06:34,750
[KYOICHI]
Must be something important.

108
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:35,875
[SATORU]
Huh?

109
00:06:35,958 --> 00:06:38,166
The Shinjuku Ward guys?

110
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:40,458
[buzzing continues]

111
00:06:45,541 --> 00:06:47,333
Kanoichi here.

112
00:06:47,416 --> 00:06:50,708
[on phone] Hey there, it's Senda
from the Shinjuku Ward Office.

113
00:06:50,791 --> 00:06:52,625
Why would you call
on the emergency line?

114
00:06:52,708 --> 00:06:55,458
[SENDA] Because you made this
an emergency.

115
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:56,833
You should take care
of your crew

116
00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:58,791
and let my boys handle
the Another.

117
00:06:58,875 --> 00:07:01,083
[SATORU] The Metro office
has jurisdiction over this,

118
00:07:01,166 --> 00:07:02,583
so stay out.

119
00:07:02,666 --> 00:07:05,291
You see, not any more.

120
00:07:05,375 --> 00:07:07,458
-[SATORU] Since when?
-Just now,

121
00:07:07,541 --> 00:07:08,958
when your bosses at City Hall

122
00:07:09,041 --> 00:07:11,083
gave up their jurisdiction
over the stadium.

123
00:07:12,125 --> 00:07:15,000
The Shinjuku Ward Nocturnal
Community Relations Division

124
00:07:15,083 --> 00:07:17,083
will be running
the show from here.

125
00:07:17,166 --> 00:07:18,833
Impossible.
Who authorized that?

126
00:07:18,916 --> 00:07:22,333
[SENDA] The Tokyo Nocturnal
Special Ordinance Committee.

127
00:07:22,416 --> 00:07:26,708
-Member Zero.
-Ah! The governor of Tokyo?

128
00:07:26,791 --> 00:07:29,125
So you can stay as long
as you're willing to do

129
00:07:29,208 --> 00:07:30,833
what we tell you.

130
00:07:30,916 --> 00:07:33,791
But you're done making
our jobs harder, am I clear?

131
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:38,375
That arrogant fool.

132
00:07:39,458 --> 00:07:41,250
Well, you gonna
make yourself useful?

133
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:42,416
Can you, even?

134
00:07:43,416 --> 00:07:45,583
You need to let her
go immediately.

135
00:07:45,666 --> 00:07:47,416
I'm going to negotiate.

136
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:50,666
[grunts softly]

137
00:07:55,250 --> 00:07:56,958
Princess Manari.

138
00:07:57,041 --> 00:07:59,458
Seimei? Hello.

139
00:07:59,541 --> 00:08:02,166
Again we meet, after so long.

140
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:03,791
Have you something to say to me?

141
00:08:03,875 --> 00:08:05,958
We've wronged you.

142
00:08:06,041 --> 00:08:08,625
I'm here to apologize
on behalf of humankind.

143
00:08:08,708 --> 00:08:12,041
[chuckles]

144
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:14,583
Am I to take solace
in these words?

145
00:08:14,666 --> 00:08:17,625
Nothing you could say or do
could ever redeem your kind.

146
00:08:17,708 --> 00:08:20,041
You lashed out in fear,
as humans always have,

147
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:21,291
and you doomed us all.

148
00:08:22,791 --> 00:08:25,458
You've slaughtered
half of my children.

149
00:08:25,541 --> 00:08:27,958
My precious little ones
are perishing in fire

150
00:08:28,041 --> 00:08:29,291
before my eyes.

151
00:08:29,375 --> 00:08:31,416
What a monstrous thing
you've done,

152
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:32,791
and for what?

153
00:08:34,958 --> 00:08:38,583
This atrocity will be felt far
beyond the walls of this nest.

154
00:08:38,666 --> 00:08:40,000
The young ones you've murdered

155
00:08:40,083 --> 00:08:41,791
were to craft offerings
to the gods.

156
00:08:41,875 --> 00:08:45,750
The cocoons you've burned were
to be spun into the finest silk.

157
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:48,333
Even if I had the number
of cocoons needed

158
00:08:48,416 --> 00:08:49,791
to produce silk now,

159
00:08:49,875 --> 00:08:52,000
there aren't enough
to spin it into thread.

160
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:55,500
There is no setting
this right, human.

161
00:08:55,583 --> 00:08:59,083
The festival at Izumo is nigh,
and I have no offering.

162
00:09:00,208 --> 00:09:02,750
For the sin of denying
the gods their silk,

163
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:06,041
they in turn shall deny us
the power of the sun.

164
00:09:06,125 --> 00:09:09,166
And so, when winter falls
upon this land...

165
00:09:10,166 --> 00:09:11,041
I'll die.

166
00:09:12,791 --> 00:09:14,250
You've wronged me!

167
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:16,000
No, you've killed me!

168
00:09:16,083 --> 00:09:17,833
Do you understand now?

169
00:09:17,916 --> 00:09:20,041
Your kind words
are worth nothing.

170
00:09:20,125 --> 00:09:21,416
I will have your lives!

171
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:23,041
For each of my children
who burns,

172
00:09:23,125 --> 00:09:24,416
so shall one of yours!

173
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:26,083
You'll atone for this
through their deaths!

174
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:27,958
Humans, if I should fall,

175
00:09:28,041 --> 00:09:30,791
my hatred will foul
the very earth itself.

176
00:09:30,875 --> 00:09:33,083
My rage will poison
the very air you breathe!

177
00:09:33,166 --> 00:09:35,125
That miasma is insane!

178
00:09:35,208 --> 00:09:36,708
Is she becoming a tatarigami?

179
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:46,541
I'll do it. I'll...
I'll take you!

180
00:09:46,625 --> 00:09:47,791
[MANARI gasps]

181
00:09:47,875 --> 00:09:50,208
And spin the silk, too!

182
00:09:50,291 --> 00:09:52,250
Manari, nobody has to die!

183
00:09:53,625 --> 00:09:56,083
You want to take me
to the festival?

184
00:09:57,083 --> 00:09:58,625
[ARATA]
Yes.

185
00:09:58,708 --> 00:10:01,541
[cackling]

186
00:10:01,625 --> 00:10:04,750
One human to do
the work of so many gods?

187
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:06,708
No, I can't do it alone.

188
00:10:06,791 --> 00:10:08,708
But I don't have to.

189
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:13,416
[MANARI]
Your friends would spin my silk?

190
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:14,666
[scoffs]

191
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:17,000
♪

192
00:10:20,041 --> 00:10:22,500
Should we fail
to arrive in time,

193
00:10:22,583 --> 00:10:26,083
you must know the fate that
will befall this land, humans.

194
00:10:26,166 --> 00:10:27,208
[ARATA]
We do.

195
00:10:29,541 --> 00:10:30,625
Then I shall wait.

196
00:10:40,541 --> 00:10:42,708
[MEN groaning]

197
00:10:42,791 --> 00:10:45,333
[SHIMIZU]
Hey! Wake up! Hey!

198
00:10:45,416 --> 00:10:46,708
[groans]

199
00:10:46,791 --> 00:10:49,333
[coughing]

200
00:10:49,416 --> 00:10:51,208
[KYOICHI]
You want us to spin the silk?

201
00:10:51,291 --> 00:10:53,333
It makes sense,
but can we really get through

202
00:10:53,416 --> 00:10:54,958
all these cocoons by dawn?

203
00:10:56,041 --> 00:10:57,875
[THEO] Did you come up
with a plan, Arata?

204
00:10:57,958 --> 00:10:59,166
Kind of.

205
00:10:59,250 --> 00:11:01,208
Or at least an idea
for a plan, I think.

206
00:11:01,291 --> 00:11:02,833
[THEO]
Uh. You think?

207
00:11:02,916 --> 00:11:05,250
I'm going to go work on it.
You guys work on the thread!

208
00:11:05,333 --> 00:11:06,458
[THEO]
Hey, hold on!

209
00:11:06,541 --> 00:11:08,625
Remember,
we're on a tight deadline!

210
00:11:08,708 --> 00:11:10,333
[ARATA]
Got it!

211
00:11:10,416 --> 00:11:13,375
How the hell are you people
acting like this is normal?

212
00:11:13,458 --> 00:11:15,333
Well, we should get to it.

213
00:11:15,416 --> 00:11:16,416
Let's go!

214
00:11:17,625 --> 00:11:22,666
♪

215
00:11:32,708 --> 00:11:34,208
All right, Senda, I'm here.

216
00:11:34,291 --> 00:11:35,625
[SENDA]
Thanks for coming.

217
00:11:35,708 --> 00:11:37,666
I know it's a long drive
from Kudanshita.

218
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:39,375
Can we skip the pleasantries?

219
00:11:39,458 --> 00:11:41,583
Right, take care
of the second floor stands.

220
00:11:41,666 --> 00:11:45,166
♪

221
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:57,458
This is something else, right?

222
00:11:57,541 --> 00:11:59,916
It seems like every agent
in Tokyo is here right now.

223
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:02,958
I'm holding the silk
of the gods in my hands.

224
00:12:03,041 --> 00:12:05,250
[YAMASHIRO]
What time is dawn, again?

225
00:12:05,333 --> 00:12:07,750
I think it was around 6:02.

226
00:12:08,916 --> 00:12:11,041
[YAMASHIRO]
So, we've just got half an hour.

227
00:12:11,125 --> 00:12:13,333
Done. Lights up.

228
00:12:18,125 --> 00:12:20,375
Don't let your guards down
for a second.

229
00:12:20,458 --> 00:12:21,875
It's still a dangerous Another!

230
00:12:25,375 --> 00:12:28,083
[THEO] Seriously, what is he
still freaking out for?

231
00:12:28,166 --> 00:12:30,041
Makes sense,
with his mindset.

232
00:12:30,125 --> 00:12:34,041
His mindset is the reason we're
all here cleaning his mess.

233
00:12:34,125 --> 00:12:37,583
♪

234
00:12:38,583 --> 00:12:39,916
[rumbling]

235
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,291
It's moving!

236
00:12:41,375 --> 00:12:43,208
Damn it, I thought
we had till dawn.

237
00:12:43,291 --> 00:12:46,416
Talk about worthless.
Ears of Sand.

238
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:48,166
-[whooshing]
-Huh?

239
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:52,208
[AGENTS murmuring]

240
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:59,916
What's this? More of them?

241
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,166
♪

242
00:13:13,541 --> 00:13:16,208
I brought some help!
We've got more hands now!

243
00:13:16,291 --> 00:13:19,000
Oh, no way. You lunatic.

244
00:13:29,166 --> 00:13:32,375
Did you really recruit
more Anothers to help us?

245
00:13:32,458 --> 00:13:33,708
[ARATA]
Just trust me.

246
00:13:33,791 --> 00:13:35,875
Okay, you guys! Let's do it!

247
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:40,625
-Hmm.
-Right.

248
00:13:40,708 --> 00:13:43,375
-Team. Let's get to work!
-[ANOTHERS] Yeah!

249
00:13:43,458 --> 00:13:46,791
[ANOTHERS chattering]

250
00:13:46,875 --> 00:13:47,916
Hey!

251
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,791
This is madness.
You expect-- Huh?

252
00:13:50,875 --> 00:13:53,750
If Arata says
his plan will work,

253
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:54,750
then we believe him.

254
00:13:54,833 --> 00:13:57,541
Hey, thanks. Yuki?

255
00:13:57,625 --> 00:13:58,500
-Huh?
-Meow.

256
00:13:58,583 --> 00:14:00,500
[grunts softly]

257
00:14:02,791 --> 00:14:04,166
I've got no issue.

258
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:06,625
The brass might want
an explanation.

259
00:14:06,708 --> 00:14:08,166
Yeah, good point.

260
00:14:09,708 --> 00:14:11,875
[TAROUBOU] I'm not obligated
to help you people.

261
00:14:11,958 --> 00:14:13,500
I can't see why I should.

262
00:14:13,583 --> 00:14:15,916
You're the ones who burned
Princess Manari's cocoons.

263
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,375
This is your problem.

264
00:14:17,458 --> 00:14:19,250
The blame falls on us.

265
00:14:19,333 --> 00:14:22,125
There's no denying it.
We screwed up.

266
00:14:22,208 --> 00:14:23,916
But we can't undo it.

267
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,916
If the princess becomes
a tatarigami,

268
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,666
many Anothers
will lose their homes.

269
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:29,583
And I don't want that to happen.

270
00:14:29,666 --> 00:14:31,958
I can't let all of you pay
for our mistakes!

271
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,458
I know I have no right
to ask you for help.

272
00:14:36,458 --> 00:14:40,083
But I don't think that
there's any other way.

273
00:14:41,541 --> 00:14:42,666
Please, Taroubou.

274
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:44,833
I'm begging you,
for everyone's sake!

275
00:14:45,833 --> 00:14:47,750
Please help us, just this once!

276
00:14:49,208 --> 00:14:50,458
[TENGU 1]
What do you guys think?

277
00:14:50,541 --> 00:14:51,750
He's not wrong.

278
00:14:51,833 --> 00:14:53,041
We're all in trouble
if the princess

279
00:14:53,125 --> 00:14:54,458
can't get
to Izumo by dawn.

280
00:14:54,541 --> 00:14:55,791
[TENGU 2]
Yeah, but I don't know.

281
00:14:55,875 --> 00:14:57,541
Why bother?

282
00:14:57,625 --> 00:14:59,083
Even if we help
them out this time,

283
00:14:59,166 --> 00:15:00,291
they'll never learn
their lesson.

284
00:15:00,375 --> 00:15:01,541
Maybe.

285
00:15:01,625 --> 00:15:02,916
But if we don't help
the humans,

286
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,375
we risk giving up our home.

287
00:15:04,458 --> 00:15:05,833
[TENGU 1]
You've got a point.

288
00:15:08,416 --> 00:15:09,958
-[TAROUBOU] All right.
-[ARATA gasps]

289
00:15:10,041 --> 00:15:12,291
♪

290
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,750
[TAROUBOU]
Get everyone ready to move out.

291
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:19,458
Seimei and I will be right back.

292
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:21,875
[ARATA screaming]

293
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:25,208
[TAROUBOU] You're going to need
all the help you can get.

294
00:15:25,291 --> 00:15:26,833
Adiel can lend a hand too.

295
00:15:26,916 --> 00:15:28,250
[ARATA]
Huh?

296
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:30,833
This is my way of repaying
your favor, Seimei.

297
00:15:30,916 --> 00:15:34,208
Sorry, wrong name.
Arata Miyako.

298
00:15:34,291 --> 00:15:36,208
Can I call on you again
when I'm in a bind?

299
00:15:36,291 --> 00:15:37,375
Will you help me out?

300
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:40,833
Yeah. It's a promise.

301
00:15:40,916 --> 00:15:42,041
Any time!

302
00:15:44,416 --> 00:15:45,666
[SENDA]
Good thinking.

303
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:48,541
You got us a lot of manpower
on short notice.

304
00:15:48,625 --> 00:15:51,375
[THEO]
Uh... Well, "Another" power.

305
00:15:51,458 --> 00:15:53,291
And we're not
getting it for free.

306
00:15:53,375 --> 00:15:55,041
We made a deal.

307
00:15:55,125 --> 00:15:56,583
The tengu made sure
they're getting something

308
00:15:56,666 --> 00:15:57,708
out of this, too.

309
00:15:58,708 --> 00:16:00,375
[ARATA] I know you said
I shouldn't make deals

310
00:16:00,458 --> 00:16:01,666
with Anothers,

311
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:02,833
but this just seemed like

312
00:16:02,916 --> 00:16:04,625
too good an opportunity
to pass up.

313
00:16:06,208 --> 00:16:08,500
My Ears. I know they can
get me in trouble

314
00:16:08,583 --> 00:16:10,708
if I'm not careful
about how I use them.

315
00:16:11,791 --> 00:16:13,375
I've learned that Anothers
have different ways

316
00:16:13,458 --> 00:16:14,833
of thinking than we do,

317
00:16:14,916 --> 00:16:17,333
and negotiating can be
as dangerous as fighting.

318
00:16:17,416 --> 00:16:19,375
But at least I can hear
their reasoning,

319
00:16:19,458 --> 00:16:21,458
even if I can't
really understand it.

320
00:16:21,541 --> 00:16:23,875
And after talking with them,
I think that angels and tengu

321
00:16:23,958 --> 00:16:25,666
might have a lot
in common with us.

322
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:28,708
[THEO]
And by "us," you mean humans?

323
00:16:28,791 --> 00:16:30,208
[ARATA]
Right.

324
00:16:30,291 --> 00:16:31,958
I think we can learn a lot
by communicating

325
00:16:32,041 --> 00:16:33,500
with humanoid Anothers.

326
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:35,875
Thanks to the Ears of Sand,

327
00:16:35,958 --> 00:16:38,000
I've gotten to hear
how they talk to each other.

328
00:16:38,083 --> 00:16:39,500
They have names
just like we do.

329
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:43,416
I want to use this power to
help us understand each other

330
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:45,583
and stop us
from having to fight.

331
00:16:45,666 --> 00:16:48,291
To make peace
between humans and Anothers,

332
00:16:48,375 --> 00:16:50,875
I think that might be
my true calling.

333
00:16:53,083 --> 00:16:54,750
[TAROUBOU]
Arata, come here a second!

334
00:16:57,375 --> 00:17:02,000
[gasping, giggling]

335
00:17:03,791 --> 00:17:10,583
♪

336
00:17:10,666 --> 00:17:13,875
[THEO] Anothers and humans,
working side by side.

337
00:17:13,958 --> 00:17:15,916
I never expected
to see that happen.

338
00:17:17,333 --> 00:17:19,000
Do you people
still not understand

339
00:17:19,083 --> 00:17:20,583
how dangerous that guy is?

340
00:17:21,708 --> 00:17:22,916
Oh, we do.

341
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,958
We actually figured it out
around the time

342
00:17:25,041 --> 00:17:28,000
an Aztec trickster god started
showing up to work with him.

343
00:17:28,083 --> 00:17:30,625
But what can you do, right?

344
00:17:30,708 --> 00:17:34,250
♪

345
00:17:34,333 --> 00:17:36,208
[THEO] I'm starting to think
we might be able to learn

346
00:17:36,291 --> 00:17:38,000
a thing or two from Arata.

347
00:17:38,083 --> 00:17:39,666
He's done a lot, hasn't he?

348
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:42,125
Maybe so, but I still have
my reservations.

349
00:17:42,208 --> 00:17:44,375
[THEO]
Oh? Yeah, such as?

350
00:17:44,458 --> 00:17:47,250
In the end, humans
and Anothers are different.

351
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:50,083
We can't do our jobs
unless we respect that.

352
00:17:50,166 --> 00:17:52,000
They're a powerful,
unpredictable force,

353
00:17:52,083 --> 00:17:53,166
something we should fear.

354
00:17:54,291 --> 00:17:55,500
I understand your view.

355
00:17:56,541 --> 00:17:58,416
You did what
you thought was best.

356
00:17:58,500 --> 00:17:59,416
That's fine.

357
00:18:01,208 --> 00:18:02,750
But Arata,

358
00:18:02,833 --> 00:18:05,125
he comes at these problems
from a whole different angle.

359
00:18:05,208 --> 00:18:07,375
I could never have imagined what
we're seeing here right now,

360
00:18:07,458 --> 00:18:09,166
and I really believe
he's the only one

361
00:18:09,250 --> 00:18:10,500
who could've made it happen.

362
00:18:14,958 --> 00:18:16,750
Okay. We're counting on you!

363
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:18,750
[inaudible dialogue]

364
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:21,916
♪

365
00:18:48,750 --> 00:18:50,916
We got it all done somehow.

366
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:51,916
Yeah.

367
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:55,666
♪

368
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:02,166
[rustling]

369
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:04,666
♪

370
00:19:17,333 --> 00:19:18,875
Mediocre work.

371
00:19:18,958 --> 00:19:20,166
I'm sorry for that.

372
00:19:21,875 --> 00:19:24,208
[MANARI]
But I shall honor my word.

373
00:19:25,416 --> 00:19:27,666
You've sinned against me.

374
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:30,083
You're callous
and eager to destroy.

375
00:19:30,166 --> 00:19:32,500
I will always see humans
in this light.

376
00:19:33,791 --> 00:19:34,958
I know.

377
00:19:35,041 --> 00:19:36,166
Even so...

378
00:19:37,208 --> 00:19:39,916
for your sake
I shall forgive their folly.

379
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:40,958
Seimei.

380
00:19:41,041 --> 00:19:43,625
[rustling]

381
00:19:49,666 --> 00:19:52,791
♪

382
00:20:06,583 --> 00:20:09,333
Thanks,
and the name's Arata.

383
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:11,125
Farewell.

384
00:20:11,208 --> 00:20:12,750
-[KOHAKU] Arata!
-Uh...

385
00:20:12,833 --> 00:20:13,625
[screams]

386
00:20:13,708 --> 00:20:15,250
[groaning]

387
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:18,166
Look at what I made!
Like it? Pretty, huh?

388
00:20:19,250 --> 00:20:22,375
This silk is just fabulous,
don't you think?

389
00:20:22,458 --> 00:20:24,208
Yeah, nice.

390
00:20:24,291 --> 00:20:25,458
I'm glad you like it,
but, you know,

391
00:20:25,541 --> 00:20:27,125
we all could have
died here, right?

392
00:20:27,208 --> 00:20:29,916
That's fun! Anyway,
I'm heading off to Izumo.

393
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,000
-[YUKI] Me, too!
-[BOTH] Yay!

394
00:20:32,083 --> 00:20:34,500
Wait, will they even allow
an Aztec god in there?

395
00:20:34,583 --> 00:20:37,125
I promise I'll get you
some really nice souvenirs!

396
00:20:37,208 --> 00:20:38,625
[YUKI]
The best!

397
00:20:38,708 --> 00:20:39,791
[BOTH]
Bye!

398
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:46,166
Well, guess we should be
on our way, too.

399
00:20:46,250 --> 00:20:48,583
Thank you
for everything, Taroubou.

400
00:20:48,666 --> 00:20:49,666
[TENGU 1]
See ya!

401
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:50,916
Thank you so much,
you guys!

402
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,083
No problem!

403
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,916
Until next time, Arata.

404
00:20:56,000 --> 00:21:00,000
♪

405
00:21:00,083 --> 00:21:01,208
[SATORU]
It worked out.

406
00:21:01,291 --> 00:21:03,791
But next time,
it could be different.

407
00:21:03,875 --> 00:21:05,958
A lot of things just happened
to go right for you.

408
00:21:07,750 --> 00:21:09,625
Don't think it will
always be like this.

409
00:21:09,708 --> 00:21:12,125
If you come at the job
like this every time,

410
00:21:12,208 --> 00:21:13,583
you're going to get hurt.

411
00:21:15,208 --> 00:21:17,958
I don't think so,
because I'm not going it alone.

412
00:21:19,166 --> 00:21:21,000
I've got the
Shinjuku Division with me.

413
00:21:22,041 --> 00:21:23,625
And we're good at our jobs.

414
00:21:23,708 --> 00:21:25,875
♪

415
00:21:25,958 --> 00:21:26,958
[SATORU chuckles wryly]

416
00:21:27,041 --> 00:21:29,791
♪

417
00:21:36,375 --> 00:21:39,000
Excellent work, Arata.
Here's a reward.

418
00:21:39,083 --> 00:21:41,833
Great job today, truly.
[chuckles]

419
00:21:41,916 --> 00:21:44,458
Of course, as we expected.

420
00:21:44,541 --> 00:21:46,250
Uh... come on, you guys.

421
00:21:46,333 --> 00:21:48,458
[SENDA]
That was a lot of work.

422
00:21:48,541 --> 00:21:49,916
What do you say we cut loose?

423
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,583
[THEO]
Ooh, yes, let's go!

424
00:21:51,666 --> 00:21:53,041
[KYOICHI] Considering
the time, you think

425
00:21:53,125 --> 00:21:54,625
we should hit up the usual spot?

426
00:21:54,708 --> 00:21:56,833
[SENDA] We should hit up
wherever we feel like.

427
00:21:56,916 --> 00:21:59,958
Metro Division is picking up
the tab, so go nuts!

428
00:22:00,041 --> 00:22:02,041
Oh, and hold onto the receipts.

429
00:22:02,125 --> 00:22:04,083
We'll need to write up
an expense report.

430
00:22:04,166 --> 00:22:05,666
In Kanoichi's name, of course.

431
00:22:05,750 --> 00:22:06,625
[ARATA]
Got it!

432
00:22:06,708 --> 00:22:08,750
[ALL laughing]

433
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:45,000
[PEOPLE chattering]

